<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">
<step><![CDATA[Preheat the oven temperature to 160C.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Place the walnuts in a food processor and process until finely ground. Add the remaining ingredients and process until smooth.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Pour the batter into a prepared 8 inch cake tin and bake for 35-45 minutes or until a skewer inserted into the centre of the cake comes out clean. Remove the cake and allow to cool for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack and cool to room temperature.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Carefully slice through the cake crosswise so that you have 2 equal halves. Spread a thick layer of jam on top of the bottom half and lay the top half of cake on top. Spread the top of the cake with another layer of jam and scatter generously with the walnuts. Cut into fat slices and serve.]]></step>
</directions>
